## [2026-03-01] - Selective Agent Retry (v0.10.35)

**What we did:** Added per-agent retry buttons so founders can retry just the one failed agent instead of restarting the entire 5-minute validation pipeline.

### 040-VRT: Selective Agent Retry (V4)

New `validator-retry` edge function with cascade dependency logic. When retrying agent X, it automatically re-runs all downstream agents (e.g., retrying ScoringAgent cascades to MVP→Composer→Verifier). Validates prerequisites are met, resets agent statuses, runs in background via `EdgeRuntime.waitUntil`, broadcasts real-time progress, and reinserts report.

Frontend: Per-agent "Retry" buttons on each failed agent card in Pipeline Summary. Smart "Retry [Agent Name]" bottom button targeting the first failed agent. Toast notifications + automatic polling resume.

- NEW `supabase/functions/validator-retry/index.ts` — Full retry logic (cascade map, prerequisite check, background execution, report reinsertion, safety net)
- NEW `supabase/functions/validator-retry/deno.json` — Deno config
- `src/pages/ValidatorProgress.tsx` — `handleRetry()`, retry buttons, smart bottom action, polling resume

---

## [2026-03-01] - Agent Tracking + Pipeline Parallelization (v0.10.34)

**What we did:** Fixed the pipeline crash on free plan (150s Deno Deploy limit) by parallelizing Research + Scoring, then wired the `validator_agent_runs` table for per-agent progress tracking end-to-end (pipeline → status endpoint → frontend).

### 038-PPO: Pipeline Parallelization + Timeout Fix

Root cause: Project on Supabase free plan (150s wall-clock) but code assumed paid plan (400s). 5 agents completed in ~120s, leaving only ~15s for Composer (needs 35s+). Deno killed the isolate at 150s.

Fix: Research + Scoring now run in parallel via `Promise.all`, saving ~31s. Pipeline deadline lowered from 300s to 140s. New critical path: ~129s total.

- `supabase/functions/validator-start/pipeline.ts` — Parallelized Research + Scoring, PIPELINE_TIMEOUT_MS 300→140s, Composer min 45→35s
- `supabase/functions/validator-start/config.ts` — Updated comments

### 039-VAR: Validator Agent Runs Tracking (V1→V3)

Wired `validator_agent_runs` table (previously 0 rows) for per-agent progress tracking:

- **V1 (Pipeline):** `db.ts` — Added `startAgentRun()`/`completeAgentRun()` helpers. `index.ts` — Pre-INSERT 7 queued rows. `pipeline.ts` — All 7 agents tracked (started→completed/failed/skipped)
- **V2 (Status):** `validator-status/index.ts` — Parallel query of `validator_agent_runs`, returns `agent_runs` array
- **V3 (Frontend):** `ValidatorProgress.tsx` — Merges `agent_runs` timing with realtime + polling (3-way priority merge)

