## [2026-02-15] - Supabase Realtime Enhancements — RT-1 through RT-8 (0.10.23)

**What we did:** Implemented 7 of 8 recommendations from the Supabase Realtime audit (`tasks/audit/24-ai-realtime.md`). Migrated from postgres_changes to broadcast pattern, added AI thinking indicators, follow-up push delivery, DB broadcast triggers, connection metrics, and broadcast replay support. RT-3 (presence) deferred — no multi-user editing yet.

### RT-1: Validator Pipeline Broadcast (Complete)

- `broadcast.ts` — shared `broadcastProgress()` helper for fire-and-forget broadcasting from edge functions
- `validator-start/pipeline.ts` — broadcasts `agent_started`, `agent_completed`, `agent_failed`, `pipeline_complete`, `pipeline_failed` events to `validator:{sessionId}` channel
- `useValidatorRealtime.ts` — new 207-line hook: 7 event handlers, progress calculation, connection metrics, follow-up state

### RT-2: AI Chat Thinking Indicator (Complete)

- `ai-chat/index.ts` — broadcasts `ai_thinking` event with `{ model, provider, startedAt }` before Gemini call
- `useRealtimeAIChat.ts` — `isThinking` + `thinkingModel` state, reset on `ai_response` receipt

### RT-4: postgres_changes → Broadcast Migration (Complete)

- `useCanvasRealtime.ts` — removed `.on('postgres_changes', ...)` listener, added `queryClient.invalidateQueries` to `canvas_saved` handler
- `usePitchDeckRealtime.ts` — removed `.on('postgres_changes', ...)` listener (already covered by `deck_ready` broadcast)

### RT-5: Follow-up Push Delivery (Complete)

- `validator-followup/index.ts` — broadcasts `followup_ready` event to `validator:{sessionId}` channel after successful response
- `useValidatorRealtime.ts` — `handleFollowupReady` handler, `onFollowupReady` callback option, `followup` state
- `useValidatorFollowup.ts` — accepts optional `{ sessionId }` options, passes to edge function

### RT-6: DB Broadcast Triggers (Complete)

- Migration `add_validator_broadcast_triggers` — enabled `pg_net` extension, created 2 trigger functions:
  - `broadcast_validator_session_change()` on `validator_sessions` (INSERT or UPDATE OF status)
  - `broadcast_validator_report_insert()` on `validator_reports` (INSERT)
  - Both use `net.http_post()` to Supabase Realtime API, EXCEPTION-wrapped to never block transactions
- `useValidatorRealtime.ts` — `handleSessionStatusChanged` + `handleReportCreated` handlers

### RT-7: Connection Quality Metrics (Complete)

- `useRealtimeChannel.ts` — `RealtimeChannelMetrics` interface: `connectedAt`, `reconnectCount`, `lastMessageAt`
- Tracked in `metricsRef` + exposed via `metrics` in return value
- Broadcast handlers update `lastMessageAt`; subscribe callback updates `connectedAt` and increments `reconnectCount`

### RT-8: Broadcast Replay (Complete)

- `useRealtimeChannel.ts` — `replay` option: `{ since: number, limit?: number }`
- Channel creation includes `config.broadcast.replay` when replay + private channel enabled
- Replays only DB-trigger broadcasts (RT-6 events), not edge function broadcasts

