## [2026-02-14] - Composer Split — 4 Parallel Section Groups (0.10.17)

**What we did:** Refactored the Composer agent from a single monolithic Gemini call into 4 focused Gemini calls (3 parallel + 1 sequential synthesis). This is task spec 021-CSP — the structural prerequisite for skill injection and notes quality improvements.

### Architecture Change

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| 1 Gemini call, 64-line prompt, 8192 tokens, 14 sections competing | 4 focused calls: Group A (Problem & Customer), Group B (Market & Risk), Group C (Execution & Economics), Group D (Executive Synthesis) |
| `extractJSON` fallback (fragile) | `responseJsonSchema` per group (strict), with `extractJSON` fallback only if Gemini returns 400 |
| All-or-nothing: 1 section fails → entire report fails | Per-group partial failure: if 1-2 groups fail, remaining sections still appear in report |
| No room for skill knowledge injection | ~30 lines of domain knowledge per group prompt |

### Composer Groups

| Group | Sections | Tokens | Parallel? |
|-------|----------|--------|-----------|
| **A** — Problem & Customer | Problem Clarity, Customer Use Case, Key Questions | 2,048 | Yes |
| **B** — Market & Risk | Market Size, Competitive Landscape, 4 Dimension Analysis, Top Threat, Risks & Assumptions | 3,072 | Yes |
| **C** — Execution & Economics | MVP Scope, Next Steps, Revenue Model, Financial Projections, Team & Hiring, Technology Stack, Resources | 3,072 | Yes |
| **D** — Executive Synthesis | Executive Summary (one-line verdict, success condition, biggest risk) | 1,024 | No (runs after A+B+C) |

### New Report Fields

| Field | Type | Source |
|-------|------|--------|
| `top_threat` | `RiskAssumptionV2` (optional) | Group B — highest-severity risk extracted for spotlight |
| `verdict_oneliner` | `string` (optional) | Group D — e.g., "High upside, execution-sensitive" |
| `success_condition` | `string` (optional) | Group D — single condition required for success |
| `biggest_risk` | `string` (optional) | Group D — single biggest risk stated explicitly |

### Bug Fix

Fixed `interviewContext` parameter bug: pipeline.ts passed 9 arguments to `runComposer()` but the function only accepted 8. Now properly accepts and passes `InterviewContext` to Groups A and D.

### Files Modified

| File | Before | After | What Changed |
|------|--------|-------|-------------|
| `agents/composer.ts` | 151 lines | 484 lines | Split into 4 `composeGroup*()` + `callGroupGemini()` + `mergeGroups()` |
| `schemas.ts` | 458 lines | 764 lines | Added `COMPOSER_GROUP_SCHEMAS` (4 group schemas) |
| `types.ts` | 188 lines | 245 lines | Added `InterviewContext`, `ComposerGroupA/B/C/D`, 4 optional fields on `ValidatorReport` |
| `config.ts` | 38 lines | 45 lines | Added `COMPOSER_GROUP_TIMEOUTS` |
| `agents/verifier.ts` | 131 lines | 145 lines | Added checks for new optional fields |

### Tests

All 304/304 tests passing. Build clean. No pipeline.ts changes needed (budget already passed dynamically).

