## Next Steps (6 Weeks)

**Recent progress:** We've laid the groundwork for a trustworthy AI system. Completed a full Supabase security audit that found 24 issues (1 critical, 2 high-priority RLS gaps). Documented all 24 edge functions and 13 dashboard screens. Built a simplified vector/RAG strategy using one knowledge_chunks table instead of overengineering with 4 libraries. Gathered Tier A research from major consulting firms—Deloitte (3,235 respondents), BCG (2,360), PwC (4,454), McKinsey, CB Insights, and Gartner. Key stats ready to load: 72% of CEOs are main AI decision-makers, $226B invested in AI in 2025, and 56% report zero financial benefit from AI yet.

**Next 6 weeks:** The goal is to make StartupAI's outputs trustworthy and professional. Week 1-2 focuses on the Coach—loading 200+ verified stats into Vector DB so every answer includes citations and confidence levels, with responses under 30 seconds. Week 3-4 upgrades the Validator to match IdeaProof's quality: 14-section reports, TAM/SAM/SOM visualizations, executive summaries with verdict labels, and market/execution factor scores. Week 5-6 adds polish: investor-ready PDF exports, shareable report links, industry benchmark overlays, and a report-context AI Copilot.

### Phase 1: Trust-First (Week 1-2)
- [ ] Load 200+ Tier A stats into Vector DB
- [ ] Coach answers with citations and confidence levels
- [ ] Speed optimization target: <30 seconds

### Phase 2: Validator (Week 3-4)
- [ ] Match IdeaProof's 14-section report format
- [ ] Add TAM/SAM/SOM visualization
- [ ] Add Executive Summary with verdict labels
- [ ] Add Highlights & Red Flags columns
- [ ] Add Market/Execution factor scores

### Phase 3: Polish (Week 5-6)
- [ ] PDF export (investor-ready)
- [ ] Share links (unique URL per report)
- [ ] Industry benchmarks overlay
- [ ] Report-context AI Copilot

